This document presents both code in R and output produced for my master’s thesis. Both spanish and english versions are available. The document presents the results from the time reduction section of the paper. Code is not shown by default, but by clicking all code buttons, all code snippets appear on screen.

Main results

The following are the main results from the output. This results correspond only to reductions in time results. For the complete set of results please review the complete paper.

  • Travel times: Treated participants reduced, on average, travel times during the intervention:
    • Complete sample: On average, treated participants reduced travel times by 10.191 minutes. See Table 1 column 2.
    • Heterogeneous effects: Participants assigned to treatment A reduced their travel times, while participants assigned to treatment B did not. Time reduction for treatment A participants was, on average, 18.794 minutes. See Table 1 column 4.
  • Treatment exposure: Exposure to treatment reduced travel times over time
    • Complete sample: Exposure to treatment, on average, decreases travel times in treated participants.
    • Heterogeneous effects: I present evidence of heterogeneous effects by treatment exposure. Particularly, Figure 1 and Figure 2 confirm results presented in Table 1. However, Figure 2 shows that treatment exposure only affects participants assigned to treatment A.

Results

This section is divided in two sections. First, I explore the program ATT using a TWFE model. Here I want determine the average effect of the treatment on the treated, The second section uses an event study approach. Here, I wish to report treatment effects by treatment exposure.

Static TWFE model

Result: Effect of transport subsidies on travel time 
df[,`Participant` := IDBASE]
df[,`Time` := semana.encuesta]

# Static twfe: Recovering the ATT sin controles
twfe.att <- feols(tiempo.viaje ~ i(trat.tfwe,tratamiento,ref = 0,ref2 = 0)|`Time` + `Participant`, data = df,vcov = ~ `Participant` + `Time`)
twfe.att.trat <- feols(tiempo.viaje ~ i(trat.tfwe,TIPOC,ref = 0,ref2 = "Control") |`Time` + `Participant`, data = df,vcov = ~ `Participant` + `Time`)

# Static twfe: Recovering the ATT con controles
twfe.att.contr <- feols(tiempo.viaje ~ i(trat.tfwe,tratamiento,ref = 0,ref2 = 0) + costo.act1.2 + i(dayofweek,ref = "Monday") + i(alternativa,ref = "Caminando") |`Time` + `Participant`, data = df,vcov = ~ `Participant` + `Time`)
twfe.att.contr.trat <- feols(tiempo.viaje ~ i(trat.tfwe,TIPOC,ref = 0,ref2 = "Control") + costo.act1.2 + i(dayofweek,ref = "Monday") + i(alternativa,ref = "Caminando") |`Time` + `Participant`, data = df,vcov = ~ `Participant` + `Time`)

mydict <- c("trat.tfwe::1:tratamiento" = "Treatment",
            "trat.tfwe::1:TIPOC::Tratamiento 1" = "Treatment A",
            "trat.tfwe::1:TIPOC::Tratamiento 2" = "Treatment B")

function.fixest.2.gt <- function(fixest.object){
df.coefss <- fixest.object$coeftable
rownames.vec <- rownames(df.coefss)
df.coefss <- as.data.frame(df.coefss)
colnames(df.coefss) <- c("estimate","se","t","p")
df.coefss <- as.data.table(df.coefss)
df.coefss[,coeff := rownames.vec]
df.coefss <- df.coefss[grepl("trat.tfwe",df.coefss$coeff)]
df.coefss[,coeff := mydict[coeff]]
df.coefss[,stars := case_when(p <= 0.01 ~ "***",
                              p <= 0.05 ~ "**",
                              p <= 0.1 ~ "*",
                              p > 0.1 ~ "")]
df.coefss[,value := paste0(round(estimate,3),stars," (",round(se,4),")")]
df.object <- dplyr::bind_rows(df.coefss[,c("coeff","value")],
                              data.frame(coeff = "Time Fixed Effects", value = "Yes"),
                              data.frame(coeff = "Participant Fixed Effects", value = "Yes"),
                              data.frame(coeff = "Controls", value = "Yes"),
                              data.frame(coeff = "S.E.: Clustered", value = "Time & Participant"),
                              data.frame(coeff = "Observations", value = as.character(round(fixest.object$nobs,0))),
                              data.frame(coeff = "R2", value = as.character(round(r2(fixest.object, "r2"),4))))
df.object <- as.data.table(df.object)
df.object[,index := 1:nrow(df.object)]
return(df.object)
}

The dependent variable in all columns is the travel time reported for each trip in the follow-up surveys. Travel time represents the aggregation of 1) travel time to the mode of transportation, 2) waiting time, and 3) commuting time. In columns 1 and 2, the treatment variable is equal to one in the follow-up survey that used the conditional treatment to be previously assigned to the treatment group, zero otherwise. On the other hand, in columns 3 and 4 the treatment variables are equal to one in the follow-up survey conditional on the amount of the subsidy to which they were chosen, zero otherwise. Columns 2 and 4 present estimates using the vector of controls *X*_{ie}. The control variables included are total commuting cost, day of the week indicator, and mode of transportation used indicator. Clustered standard errors by person and follow-up survey number are presented in parentheses.")) %>%

colors.cs.plot <- c("Tratamiento A" = "#8a0101","Tratamiento B" = "#707070")
